\lambda
 \pm \frac{dy}{\sqrt{k y - \beta}} = dx,
k = \sigma g /C
\beta = 1-\lambda/C
 \pm \frac{dy}{\beta^2 \sqrt{\frac{ky}{\beta} - 1}} = dx,
z:= ky/\beta
dy = \beta dz/k 
 \pm \frac{dz}{k \beta \sqrt{z-1}} = dx,
 \pm \frac{2 \sqrt{z-1}}{k \beta} = x + A,
A
z = z(x)
z(x) = 1+ \left( \frac{k\beta}{2} \right)^2 \left(x+A\right)^2.
